#. <section class="sutta" id="sn24.1"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn24.1:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 24"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 24"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn24.1:0.2"
msgid "1. Sotāpattivagga"
msgstr "1. Stream-Entry"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn24.1:0.3"
msgid "1. Vātasutta"
msgstr "1. Winds"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.202"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn24.1:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane."
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove. "

msgctxt "sn24.1:1.2"
msgid "Bhagavā etadavoca:"
msgstr "The Buddha said this:"

msgctxt "sn24.1:1.3"
msgid ""
"“kismiṃ nu kho, bhikkhave, sati, kiṃ upādāya, kiṃ abhinivissa evaṃ diṭṭhi "
"uppajjati:"
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, when what exists, because of grasping what and insisting on "
"what, does the view arise:"

msgctxt "sn24.1:1.4"
msgid ""
"‘na vātā vāyanti, na najjo sandanti, na gabbhiniyo vijāyanti, na "
"candimasūriyā udenti vā apenti vā esikaṭṭhāyiṭṭhitā’”ti?"
msgstr ""
"‘Winds don’t blow; rivers don’t flow; pregnant women don’t give birth; the "
"moon and stars neither rise nor set, but stand firm like a pillar.’”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn24.1:2.1"
msgid ""
"“Bhagavaṃmūlakā no, bhante, dhammā bhagavaṃnettikā bhagavaṃpaṭisaraṇā. Sādhu "
"vata, bhante, bhagavantaññeva paṭibhātu etassa bhāsitassa attho. Bhagavato "
"sutvā bhikkhū dhāressantī”ti."
msgstr ""
"“Our teachings are rooted in the Buddha. He is our guide and our refuge. "
"Sir, may the Buddha himself please clarify the meaning of this. The "
"mendicants will listen and remember it.”"

msgctxt "sn24.1:2.2"
msgid "“Tena hi, bhikkhave, suṇātha, sādhukaṃ manasi karotha, bhāsissāmī”ti."
msgstr "“Well then, mendicants, listen and pay close attention, I will speak.”"

msgctxt "sn24.1:2.3"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ."
msgstr "“Yes, sir,” they replied."

msgctxt "sn24.1:2.4"
msgid "Bhagavā etadavoca:"
msgstr "The Buddha said this:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.203"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn24.1:3.1"
msgid ""
"“Rūpe kho, bhikkhave, sati, rūpaṃ upādāya, rūpaṃ abhinivissa evaṃ diṭṭhi "
"uppajjati:"
msgstr ""
"“When form exists, because of grasping form and insisting on form, the view "
"arises:"

msgctxt "sn24.1:3.2"
msgid ""
"‘na vātā vāyanti, na najjo sandanti, na gabbhiniyo vijāyanti, na "
"candimasūriyā udenti vā apenti vā esikaṭṭhāyiṭṭhitā’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘Winds don’t blow; rivers don’t flow; pregnant women don’t give birth; the "
"moon and stars neither rise nor set, but stand firm like a pillar.’"

msgctxt "sn24.1:3.3"
msgid "Vedanāya sati … pe …"
msgstr "When feeling …"

msgctxt "sn24.1:3.4"
msgid "saññāya sati …"
msgstr "perception …"

msgctxt "sn24.1:3.5"
msgid "saṅkhāresu sati …"
msgstr "choices …"

msgctxt "sn24.1:3.6"
msgid ""
"viññāṇe sati, viññāṇaṃ upādāya, viññāṇaṃ abhinivissa evaṃ diṭṭhi uppajjati:"
msgstr ""
"consciousness exists, because of grasping consciousness and insisting on "
"consciousness, the view arises:"

msgctxt "sn24.1:3.7"
msgid ""
"‘na vātā vāyanti, na najjo sandanti, na gabbhiniyo vijāyanti, na "
"candimasūriyā udenti vā apenti vā esikaṭṭhāyiṭṭhitā’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘Winds don’t blow; rivers don’t flow; pregnant women don’t give birth; the "
"moon and stars neither rise nor set, but stand firm like a pillar.’"

msgctxt "sn24.1:3.8"
msgid "Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, bhikkhave, "
msgstr "What do you think, mendicants? "

msgctxt "sn24.1:3.9"
msgid "rūpaṃ niccaṃ vā aniccaṃ vā”ti?"
msgstr "Is form permanent or impermanent?”"

msgctxt "sn24.1:3.10"
msgid "“Aniccaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“Impermanent, sir.”"

msgctxt "sn24.1:3.11"
msgid "“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vā taṃ sukhaṃ vā”ti?"
msgstr "“But if it’s impermanent, is it suffering or happiness?”"

msgctxt "sn24.1:3.12"
msgid "“Dukkhaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“Suffering, sir.”"

msgctxt "sn24.1:3.13"
msgid ""
"“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vipariṇāmadhammaṃ, api nu taṃ anupādāya evaṃ diṭṭhi "
"uppajjeyya:"
msgstr ""
"“But by not grasping what’s impermanent, suffering, and perishable, would "
"the view arise:"

msgctxt "sn24.1:3.14"
msgid ""
"‘na vātā vāyanti, na najjo sandanti, na gabbhiniyo vijāyanti, na "
"candimasūriyā udenti vā apenti vā esikaṭṭhāyiṭṭhitā’”ti?"
msgstr ""
"‘Winds don’t blow; rivers don’t flow; pregnant women don’t give birth; the "
"moon and stars neither rise nor set, but stand firm like a pillar’?”"

msgctxt "sn24.1:3.15"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“No, sir.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn24.1:4.1"
msgid "“Vedanā niccā vā aniccā vā”ti …"
msgstr "“Is feeling …"

msgctxt "sn24.1:4.2"
msgid "“saññā …"
msgstr "perception …"

msgctxt "sn24.1:4.3"
msgid "saṅkhārā …"
msgstr "choices …"

msgctxt "sn24.1:4.4"
msgid "viññāṇaṃ niccaṃ vā aniccaṃ vā”ti?"
msgstr "consciousness permanent or impermanent?”"

msgctxt "sn24.1:4.5"
msgid "“Aniccaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“Impermanent, sir.”"

msgctxt "sn24.1:4.6"
msgid "“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vā taṃ sukhaṃ vā”ti?"
msgstr "“But if it’s impermanent, is it suffering or happiness?”"

msgctxt "sn24.1:4.7"
msgid "“Dukkhaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“Suffering, sir.”"

msgctxt "sn24.1:4.8"
msgid ""
"“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vipariṇāmadhammaṃ, api nu taṃ anupādāya evaṃ diṭṭhi "
"uppajjeyya:"
msgstr ""
"“But by not grasping what’s impermanent, suffering, and perishable, would "
"the view arise:"

msgctxt "sn24.1:4.9"
msgid ""
"‘na vātā vāyanti, na najjo sandanti, na gabbhiniyo vijāyanti, na "
"candimasūriyā udenti vā apenti vā esikaṭṭhāyiṭṭhitā’”ti?"
msgstr ""
"‘Winds don’t blow; rivers don’t flow; pregnant women don’t give birth; the "
"moon and stars neither rise nor set, but stand firm like a pillar’?”"

msgctxt "sn24.1:4.10"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“No, sir.”"

# BB calls this the “tetrad of sense objects”. Except it’s a septad not a tetrad; it deals largely with cognitive not sense experience; and there is no mention, here or elsewhere in the EBTs, of “objects”. BB’s explanations of this group show the extent to which it has simply been not listened to by the tradition, concerned only with fitting it into the major categories. But it appears in this specific context for an important reason: it deals, not with sense experience in general, but with the ways in which religious and philosophical views are acquired.
#. VAR: Yampidaṃ → yamidaṃ (aññattha)
msgctxt "sn24.1:4.11"
msgid ""
"“Yampidaṃ diṭṭhaṃ sutaṃ mutaṃ viññātaṃ pattaṃ pariyesitaṃ anuvicaritaṃ "
"manasā tampi niccaṃ vā aniccaṃ vā”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“That which is seen, heard, thought, cognized, searched, and explored by the "
"mind: is that permanent or impermanent?”"

msgctxt "sn24.1:4.12"
msgid "“Aniccaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“Impermanent, sir.”"

msgctxt "sn24.1:4.13"
msgid "“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vā taṃ sukhaṃ vā”ti?"
msgstr "“But if it’s impermanent, is it suffering or happiness?”"

msgctxt "sn24.1:4.14"
msgid "“Dukkhaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“Suffering, sir.”"

msgctxt "sn24.1:4.15"
msgid ""
"“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vipariṇāmadhammaṃ, api nu taṃ anupādāya evaṃ diṭṭhi "
"uppajjeyya:"
msgstr ""
"“But by not grasping what’s impermanent, suffering, and perishable, would "
"the view arise:"

msgctxt "sn24.1:4.16"
msgid ""
"‘na vātā vāyanti, na najjo sandanti, na gabbhiniyo vijāyanti, na "
"candimasūriyā udenti vā apenti vā esikaṭṭhāyiṭṭhitā’”ti?"
msgstr ""
"‘Winds don’t blow; rivers don’t flow; pregnant women don’t give birth; the "
"moon and stars neither rise nor set, but stand firm like a pillar’?”"

msgctxt "sn24.1:4.17"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“No, sir.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
#. VAR: ariyasāvakassa imesu ca → imesu chasu (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "sn24.1:5.1"
msgid ""
"“Yato kho, bhikkhave, ariyasāvakassa imesu ca ṭhānesu kaṅkhā pahīnā hoti, "
"dukkhepissa kaṅkhā pahīnā hoti, dukkhasamudayepissa kaṅkhā pahīnā hoti, "
"dukkhanirodhepissa kaṅkhā pahīnā hoti, dukkhanirodhagāminiyā paṭipadāyapissa "
"kaṅkhā pahīnā hoti—"
msgstr ""
"“When a noble disciple has given up doubt in these six cases, and has given "
"up doubt in suffering, its origin, its cessation, and the practice that "
"leads to its cessation,"

msgctxt "sn24.1:5.2"
msgid ""
"ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, ariyasāvako sotāpanno avinipātadhammo niyato "
"sambodhiparāyano”ti."
msgstr ""
"they’re called a noble disciple who is a stream-enterer, not liable to be "
"reborn in the underworld, bound for awakening.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn24.1:5.3"
msgid "Paṭhamaṃ."
msgstr ""
